<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-09-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-09-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79620 Boeing Airplane Co./35:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-28T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 28, 1928—6
                                    p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>64. Department’s 38, September 26, 3 p.m. Lawyer who holds O’Neil’s
                                power of attorney saw Director of Posts and Telegraphs this morning
                                and was advised that no contracts could be consummated in short time
                                remaining of present administration. He advised waiting till matter
                                could be taken up with new government. O’Neil’s lawyer counsels
                                deferring further action until appointment of new Director of Posts
                                and Telegraphs.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>